<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 97.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-30"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 30, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Referring to your despatch of the 28th
                            ultimo, No. 40, and to my reply of the 23d instant, No. 79, in regard to
                            insurgent piratical movements and schemes in Europe, I have now to
                            inform you that, by a letter of yesterday, the Secretary of the Navy
                            informs me that the Kearsarge, now at Boston, has been ordered to
                            proceed to the coast of Europe for the purpose of co-operating with the
                            vessels now engaged in watching the movements of the Stonewall, and will
                            use all possible despatch in reaching her destination.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWED.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c. Paris.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>